{{Infobox venue | name = National Theatre of Karelia | nickname = | native_name = Karjalan kansallinen teatteri | native_name_lang = fi | fullname = | former names = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Petrozavodsk 06-2017 img19 Karelian National Theatre.jpg | image_size = 300px | image_alt = | caption = | pushpin_map = | pushpin_map_caption = | pushpin_label_position = | address = Karl Marx prospect 19, [[Petrozavodsk]], [[Russia]] | coordinates = {{coord|61|47|14|N|34|22|47|E|type:landmark_region:RU|display=inline,title}} | type = Theatre | genre = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1932 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | production = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | seating_type = | capacity = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | field_shape = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = {{URL|http://teatr.onego.ru}} | publictransit = }} '''National Theatre of Karelia''' ({{lang-fi|Karjalan kansallinen teatteri}}, {{lang-ru|Национа́льный теа́тр Республики Каре́лия}}) is a 1932 established [[theatre]] in [[Petrozavodsk]], [[Republic of Karelia]], [[Russia]]. It is the only [[Finnish language]] theatre in Russia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visitpetrozavodsk.ru/en/places_and_events/places1/theaters/nacionalnyj_teatr_respubliki_kareliya/|title=The National Theatre of the Republic of Karelia|author=|publisher=Visit Petrozavodsk|date=|accessdate=4 April 2017|language=}}</ref>
