{{Sculpture | image = [[File:POL MDM Muzyka3.jpg|240px]] | title = The Music Group | artist = [[Józef Gosławski (Polish sculptor)|Józef Gosławski]] | year = 1952 | city = [[Image:Flag of Poland.svg|20px]] [[Poland]], [[Warsaw]] | museum = }} '''''The Music''''' (also known as ''The Music Group'', [[Polish language|Polish]]: ''Muzyka'', ''Grupa Muzyka'') is one of three sculptures<ref>Except ''Music'' there are also ''Fine Arts'' and ''Theatre'' groups.</ref> located on the roof of the building on Koszykowa Street 34/50 in [[Warsaw]] since 1952. The project was chosen after an artistic competition. The monument was designed by [[Józef Gosławski (Polish sculptor)|Józef Gosławski]], but his wife - [[Wanda Gosławska|Wanda]] - and his brother - [[Stanisław Gosławski|Stanisław]] - helped him with its realization because of the short deadline. Lack of scaffolds, problems with obtaining funds and the short deadline forced the artists<ref>Except Józef Gosławski sculptures in new Warsaw district were designed by [[Kazimierz Bieńkowski]] and [[Leon Machowski]].</ref> to write a letter to the chief architect of Warsaw - Józef Sigalin. After that, the conditions were improved and work was completed on time.<ref name="Heritage">{{cite journal|author=Anna Rudzka|date=July 2008|title=It's worth looking up...|journal=Zabytki. Heritage|volume=7 | issue = 30 |pages=6–9|publisher=Przedsiębiorstwo Wydawnicze Rzeczpospolita SA|location=Warsaw|issn=1640-0194}}</ref>
The image of ''Music Group'' was on one of the postcards published in 1952. It cost 1.30 [[Polish złoty|zł]], of which 0.08 [[Polish złoty|zł]] was spent on ''The Social Fund of Reconstruction of Capital City''.<ref name="Heritage"/>
