{{italic title}} {{Infobox television |show_name = '''''WWE Wal3ooha''''' |image = File:WWE Wal3ooha logo.jpg |genre = {{Plainlist| * [[Sports entertainment]] * [[Professional wrestling]] }} |creator = [[Vince McMahon]] |country = [[United Arab Emirates]] |num_seasons = 3 |num_episodes = 75 (as of {{Start date|2017|10|4}})<!-- DO NOT change until end of current episode airs. --> |camera = [[Multiple-camera setup|Multicamera setup]] | runtime = | company = [[WWE]] | network = [[OSN Sports]] {{small|({{Start date|2017}} – present)}} | picture_format = | first_aired = {{Start date|2017|05|04}} | last_aired = present | preceded_by = | related = {{Plainlist| * ''[[WWE Bottom Line|Bottom Line]]'' * ''[[WWE Experience|Experience]]'' * ''[[WWE Afterburn|Afterburn]]'' * ''[[WWE Vintage|Vintage]]'' * ''[[WWE Free for All|Free For All]]'' * ''[[List of former WWE television programming#Raw Sunday Dhamaal (2015–2017)|Raw Sunday Dhamaal]]'' }} | website = http://www.osn.com/en-ae/explore/current-offers/wwe-wal3ooha }}
'''''[[WWE]] Wal3ooha''''' is a [[Middle East]]ern [[television program]] produced by [[WWE]] which mainly features recaps of ''[[WWE Raw|Raw]]'' and ''[[WWE SmackDown|SmackDown Live]]'' as well as exclusive interviews with WWE superstars and personalities. The show is broadcast on [[OSN Sports]] in the [[United Arab Emirates]] every Thursday at 8:00pm KSA.<ref name=Mania>{{Cite web|url=http://411mania.com/wrestling/wwe-announces-details-on-arabic-show-wal3ooha/|title=WWE Announces Details on Arabic Show ‘Wal3ooha’|last=Thomas|first=Jeremy|website=411Mania.com}}</ref> The show's title translates to “light it up”<ref name=Mania/> and is the first WWE program to feature original and localized content intended exclusively for Middle Eastern markets.<ref name=Mania/><ref>{{Cite web|title=Details On New 'WWE Wal3ooha' Arabic Show, Stephanie McMahon Comments, Next WWE Network Collection|url=http://www.wrestlinginc.com/wi/news/2017/0430/625724/details-on-new-wwe-wal3ooha-arabic-show/|last=Thomas|first=Marc|website=Wrestlinginc.com}}</ref>
==Hosts== {| class="wikitable" !Year(s) !Hosts |- |May 4, 2017–present |[[Moein Al Bastaki]] and Nathalie Mamo<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.wwe.com/worldwide/article/osn-wwe-announce-new-weekly-arabic-show-wwe-wal3ooha|title=OSN and WWE announce exclusive new weekly Arabic show "WWE Wal3ooha"|last=WWE.com|first=Staff|website=WWE.com}}</ref> |}
==Reception== The reception to the program from fans in the [[Arab world]] has been positive thus far.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/black_cel/status/863684351485149185|title=blackCel on Twitter|quote=Two weeks has passed with the premiere of the show @WWEWAL3OOHA, The reception has been great we can't wait for more.|website=[[Twitter]]}}</ref>
